    "ideation": "The shrug is the ultimate expression of 'I have no idea.' The performance needs to capture the physical rising of the shoulders through the rising of the eye lids and gaze, followed by the resigned fall. The eyes start neutral, then lift in a wide, slightly helpless arch with a blank stare, while the mouth enters a specific 'unfazed' state—not quite a frown, not quite a smile, but a flat wave with slightly raised corners (smirk-ish phase). The animation concludes with a slow, downward gaze and a sigh-like color shift to indicate the matter is closed and forgotten. Color transitions from curious gold to a dusty, faded slate blue.",
